Note on bundled software:

This MIT license covers only the wrapper assets in this repository
(Dockerfile, rootfs/, scripts, Unraid templates, README, banner / icon
artwork derived from public-domain sources). It does NOT relicense the
software shipped inside the resulting container image.

In particular:

  * Krusader itself remains licensed under GPL-3.0-or-later
    (https://invent.kde.org/utilities/krusader)
  * Kate, Konsole, Ark, Breeze and other KDE components retain their
    upstream licenses (mostly GPL-2.0+ / LGPL-2.1+).
  * The LinuxServer.io baseimage-kasmvnc base image retains its own
    license terms (GPL-3.0).
  * The unrar tool is shipped under its non-free upstream license.

When you run, distribute or rebuild the resulting container image, you
must comply with the licenses of all bundled components, not only with
this MIT license.
